  ## Config 1
  
  You can also use the zsh `vcs_info`module to obtain the git information. This example will enable the exact same prompt output as Config 0. This is slightly less readable (IMO) but makes it a lot easier to obtain and use various other information from git to use in your prompt if you wish.
  
  For an example of some basic additional config options using this module you can learn from this post:
  
  [**Customize your ZSH prompt with vcs\_info** \\
  \\
  **By Arjan van der Gaag on Dec 23 2011. Tagged Git, ZSH, vcs\_info. You're not cool if you're don't display some Git…**\\
  \\
  arjanvandergaag.nl](https://arjanvandergaag.nl/blog/customize-zsh-prompt-with-vcs-info.html?source=post_page-----3d01602a6f33---------------------------------------)
  
  You can also read the zsh docs for this\[1\].
  
  ## Oh My Zsh
  
  [**Oh My Zsh — a delightful & open source framework for Zsh** \\
  \\
